[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Recommendations[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The independent retail sector in Northern Ireland is one of the most innovative, vibrant, varied and important - but it is also one of the most fragile. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Lacking the critical mass and resources of the large multiples, 
[normal]independent traders can be more susceptible to economic changes. Of those we surveyed who tried to access finance in the last three years, 35% were unsuccessful. This is concer
[normal]ning. We need a banking system 
[normal]which better understands small retailers. Our mem
[normal]bers are a key driver of growth in Northern Ireland and efficient funding and support is vital to our sector in supporting economic recovery.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We would 
[normal]make the following recommendations
[normal]:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Northern Ireland Banking Forum[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]As Banking regulations are not a devolved matter, we suggest that the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland establish and Chair a 
[normal]NI Banking Forum
[normal]. This would include representatives from the Banks, Business Organisations and Executive Ministers for Ente
[normal]rprise and Finance.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We envisage this Forum to be a mechanism to promote good communication and indeed to resolve any issues such as we have identified in our survey. This Forum should meet at least twice a year.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Branch Vacancy Strategy[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Bank b
[normal]ranch
[normal]es are
[normal] a
[normal]n
[normal] essential element in our High Streets and Town Centres, both in terms of generating footfall and service provision for local traders.
[normal] All the banks need to ensure that 
[normal]there is 
[normal]adequate consultation with local stakeholders in advance of any intended cl
[normal]osures.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]With the high volume of bank branch closures in Northern Ireland we need all banks to commit themselves to a target of alternative use of the empty buildings within three months of closure.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Alternative use such a new retail store, pop up shop, or
[normal] being used a communi
[normal]ty group will boost 
[normal]the 
[normal]footfall which the branch closure has reduced. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Overdrafts and Credit Cards[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]As evidenced in our survey B
[normal]anks unilaterally changing the o
[normal]verdrafts of our members is still a cause for concern. We recommend a tig
[normal]htening of regulations covering the conditions on Overdraft and Credit cards to ensure that small business customers are not negatively impacted by any 
[normal]such 
[normal]changes.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We would recommend that 
[normal]the 
[normal]Financial Conduct Authority examine this area as a matter of
[normal] priority.
